  <p>Masculine anthroponymic proper nouns name male persons, e.g. <mark>Seumas</mark>
    <en>James</en>, <mark>Dòmhnall</mark>
    <en>Donald</en>. They are unchanged in the dative case, and are both slenderised and lenited in the genitive, e.g. <mark>le Seumas</mark>
    <en>with James</en>, <mark>taigh Sheumais</mark>
    <en>James’ house</en>. <boxlink ref="#masculine_anthroponyms"/></p>
